{{see|Smith}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[smiþ]]'', from Germanic ''*smiþaz''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[smid]]'', German ''[[Schmied]]'', Swedish ''[[smed]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/smɪθ/}}
*{{SAMPA|/smIT/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪθ|-ɪθ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A [[craftsperson]] who works [[metal]] into desired forms using a [[hammer]] and other tools, sometimes heating the metal to make it more [[workable]].

